#input explained
#input is a function
#it allows a user to input data into
#...a program via the keyboard
#it can also display strings

#here is a variable
name = ""
#here is a variable with input
name = input("enter name")
#this will display "enter name"
#the user should then enter a string
#then press enter
#the data entered will be stored in the variable

#this data can be displayed later
print(name)

name = input("enter your name")
age = input("enter your age")
favColour = input("enter your favourite colour")

print("Hello", name, "you are", age, "years old and your favourite colour is", favColour)
#this asks the user's name, age and favourite colour and displays them.
